GUARD KEITH SMITH IS CUT BY LAKERS 
The Lakers waived free-agent rookie Keith Smith, a guard from the University of 
California, reducing their roster to 13 Tuesday. 
One more player must be cut by Thursday. Coach Mike Dunleavy will choose 
between veteran forward Tony Brown, free-agent rookie forward Irving Thomas and 
guard Tony Smith, a second-round draft choice. 
Keith Smith played in three exhibitions, games, making four of six shots. The 
Lakers will open the season Saturday against the Spurs at San Antonio. MARK 
HEISLER 
